  "market_context": "The market was in a clear downtrend; the analyst instructed viewers to locate a hammer pattern near a visible support level (gray horizontal bar at bottom of chart).",
  "key_observation": "A green candle with a small real body and a long lower wick—approximately 2x to 4x the body length—appeared at support, followed by an upward price reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst defined the hammer as a single-candle bullish reversal pattern requiring a small real body and a long lower wick (at least 2x body length, preferably 3–4x).",
    "Step 2: The analyst emphasized that the upper wick should be very small or absent, and the pattern must occur after a downtrend.",
    "Step 3: The analyst gave hints: hammer real body can be green or red, and it typically forms near a support level.",
    "Step 4: The analyst revealed the hammer on the chart—a green candle with long lower wick positioned at the gray support zone—and confirmed the subsequent upside reversal."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reversed upward after the hammer formed; no specific trade entry/exit or P/L was stated.",
  "lessons": "A valid hammer requires strict structural criteria (small body, long lower wick, minimal upper wick) and contextual confirmation (downtrend + support proximity) to signal a reliable bullish reversal.",
